Class TimeoutTab

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.debug.ui.AbstractLaunchConfigurationTab
      • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.gui.TimeoutTab
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.debug.ui.ILaunchConfigurationTab, org.eclipse.debug.ui.ILaunchConfigurationTab2

    public class TimeoutTab
extends org.eclipse.debug.ui.AbstractLaunchConfigurationTab
    A tab of Beagle's launch configuration allowing the user to choose between an adaptive timeout, a constant timeout, or no timeout at all.

      • BEAGLE_LAUNCH_CONFIGURATION_TIMEOUT_TYPE

        public static final String BEAGLE_LAUNCH_CONFIGURATION_TIMEOUT_TYPE
        The key in the Beagle Launch Configuration determining the type of the timeout to be used.

        Permitted values are:

        • BEAGLE_LAUNCH_CONFIGURATION_TIMEOUT_TYPE_VALUE_ADAPTIVE_TIMEOUT
        • BEAGLE_LAUNCH_CONFIGURATION_TIMEOUT_TYPE_VALUE_CONSTANT_TIMEOUT
        • BEAGLE_LAUNCH_CONFIGURATION_TIMEOUT_TYPE_VALUE_NO_TIMEOUT
